  "body": "End-of-session closeout for the Claude For Chrome capture work on 2026-05-22. Three components shipped: core/ (shared envelope emitter), server/ (Node HTTP bridge with /transcript and /relay endpoints), claude-for-chrome/ (MV3 extension for claude.ai-in-a-tab + DevTools Snippet for the Anthropic Sidepanel). Five load-bearing learnings recorded: (1) Chrome's cross-extension isolation blocks scripting/debugger access to other extensions' pages — only DevTools console is left open as a seam, (2) Sidepanel CSP blocks direct localhost fetch, but not navigation, so window.open to a relay page with hash-payload works, (3) of three capture paths considered, the Chrome Snippets path was the right pragmatic choice over chrome.debugger (blocked) and --remote-debugging-port (security tradeoff), (4) DOM selectors documented by brother-Claude two days prior were still accurate, (5) source_url-based update-in-place semantics work cleanly. Outstanding cosmetic items: session_arc misses tabId, subject is frozen across in-place updates. Full design rationale, rejected alternatives, and follow-up items in the sibling .body.md.",

